>[Thoughts]
>2^(te-Ta)/10

Hi Jerry.

thanks for writing to the Math Forum.

The caret (^) is used to designate an exponent:

  3^4 = 3 to the fourth power
      = 3 x 3 x 3 x 3
                                                        4
This method is used so that we don't have to resort to 3
using two lines.

- Doctor Douglas, The Math Forum
  <http://mathforum.org/dr.math/>

